div.div:
- The product spec does not need to be complete or totally correct when initially released. It is meant to evolve iteratively
- In each iteration, the business spec must be drafted first, then teams derive other artifacts based on it. Otherwise chaos.Â
- Developers should not expect the business colleagues to dig into your code to find out the truth. If you have any change wishes to the spec, please tell the business team first, and wait for them to update the spec first (or update the business spec yourself upon an agreement with the business team).Â
- All artifacts should be stored (versionized) in GitLab, and use CI/CD pipeline to any automate DevSecOps processes as far as possible
- Documents should use an ASCII format (Markdown or other similar format) to enable Git versionization and further pipelines. The source files of documents canÂ be transformed into HTML and automatically deployed to a document/HTTP server, or can be viewed in GitLab as they are.Â
